<div class="description">
    <h3>Description</h3>

    <div class="body">
        <p>Most all line endings in our generated PDF documents use a single linefeed character (LF - 0x0A). However, in a couple of places, a carriage return-linefeed sequence (CRLF - 0x0D 0x0A) is used. Both are legal in PDF, but the single linefeed is recommended.</p>

<p>For consistency, change all occurrences of CRLF to LF.</p>

